                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Burst radius is affected by Ability Range ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Damage dealt is based on the percentage of the target's total unarmored health (including Shields ) after the Nervos first attaches (e.g. it will deal 80% of the target's health (minus the attachment damage) upon death if it attached when the target was at 80% health)."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Damage to health can be from any source; it does not have to be damage dealt by Nervos."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Damage is unaffected by Ability Strength ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Damage is dealt per attached Nervos (e.g. if 4 Nervos attach to a target at 100% health, they will each deal 100% of the target's health (minus the attachment damage) upon death)"
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Only deals damage to those it has Line of Sight to."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Total damage from a single Nervos uncommonly reaches 100% of the enemy's health, as the initial attachment damage is inflicted before the health is set (e.g. if the Nervos deals 25 damage per second, and attaches to an enemy with 100 health, it will only be able to deal a 75 damage burst upon death)."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The 100% health damage can only be achieved if enemies were invulnerable while getting attached (e.g. certain Deep Archimedea conditions), or if an enemy has an amount of Overguard equal to, or greater than, the Nervos' damage (e.g. if the Nervos deals 25 damage per second, and it attaches to an enemy with 100 health and 25 or more Overguard, it will be able to deal a 100 damage burst upon death)."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Tesla Bank",
                  "pageId": 1459231,
                  "revisionId": 2745578,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "This also means that enemies killed by the first instance of damage will not cause any radial burst."
                }
              },
